@SamirTalwar It's all pluggable middlewares in Express. Not a lot out of the box.
But it's not awesome, if you like TypeScript.
But simple and gets you quite far without needing to worry.

@SamirTalwar I have a project I am working on with a lightweight webserver for running surveys here.
The server setup starts here: https://t.co/xfK5gCtlA9

Most tests are integration tests that set up their own small webserver: https://t.co/0Af7JcjHjC

I think this is typically done in the refactoring step of TDD but I've seen that it helps to "sketch" the new business logic first using calls to helper functions:

function addMemberToGroup(member, group) {
  if(!isMember(member, group)) {
    addMember(member, group)
  }
}
